abstract_summ: Thirty maxillary anterior teeth in human cadavers were selected and non-surgical root canal treatment was performed on these teeth . A standardized 4-mm osteotomy and a 3-mm root resection with as close to a zero-degree bevel as possible was made on each tooth . Micro-CT scans were taken and analyzed for volume and percentage of residual obturation material at 5- and 10-mm .
